%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Does%20Aspartame%20Really%20Cause%20Cancer%3F%20What%20The%20WHO%20Listing%20Means%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Agency%20for%20Research%20on%20Cancer%20(IARC)%2C%20which%20is%20the%20specialised%20cancer%20agency%20of%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%2C%20has%20declared%20aspartame%20may%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews%2Fitem%2F14-07-2023-aspartame-hazard-and-risk-assessment-results-released%5C%22%3Epossible%20carcinogenic%20hazard%20to%20humans%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20branch%20of%20the%20WHO%2C%20the%20Joint%20WHO%20and%20Food%20and%20Agriculture%20Organization's%20Expert%20Committee%20on%20Food%20Additives%20has%20assessed%20the%20risk%20and%20developed%20recommendations%20on%20how%20much%20aspartame%20is%20safe%20to%20consume.%20They%20have%20recommended%20the%20acceptable%20daily%20intake%20be%200%20to%2040mg%20per%20kilo%20of%20body%20weight%2C%20as%20we%20currently%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foodstandards.gov.au%2Fconsumer%2Fadditives%2Faspartame%2FPages%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%3Ein%20Australia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20hazard%20is%20different%20to%20a%20risk.%20The%20hazard%20rating%20means%20it's%20an%20agent%20that%20is%20capable%20of%20causing%20cancer%3B%20a%20risk%20measures%20the%20likelihood%20it%20could%20cause%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20does%20this%20hazard%20assessment%20mean%20for%20you%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EFirstly%2C%20what%20is%20aspartame%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foodstandards.gov.au%2Fconsumer%2Fadditives%2Faspartame%2FPages%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%3EAspartame%20is%20an%20artificial%20sweetener%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20is%20200%20times%20sweeter%20than%20sugar%2C%20but%20without%20any%20kilojoules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20used%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foodstandards.gov.au%2Fconsumer%2Fadditives%2Faspartame%2FPages%2Fdefault.aspx%5C%22%3Evariety%20of%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20carbonated%20drinks%20such%20as%20Coke%20Zero%2C%20Diet%20Coke%2C%20Pepsi%20Max%20and%20some%20home%20brand%20offerings.%20You%20can%20identify%20aspartame%20in%20drinks%20and%20foods%20by%20looking%20for%20additive%20number%20951.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFood%20products%20such%20as%20yogurt%20and%20confectionery%20may%20also%20contain%20aspartame%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20stable%20at%20warm%20temperatures%20and%20thus%20not%20used%20in%20baked%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommercial%20names%20of%20aspartame%20include%20Equal%2C%20Nutrasweet%2C%20Canderel%20and%20Sugar%20Twin.%20In%20Australia%20the%20acceptable%20daily%20intake%20is%2040mg%20per%20kilo%20of%20body%20weight%20per%20day%2C%20which%20is%20about%2060%20sachets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Ffood-additives-petitions%2Faspartame-and-other-sweeteners-food%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DHow%2520many%2520packets%2520can%2520a%2Cbased%2520on%2520its%2520sweetness%2520intensity%253F%26amp%3Btext%3DNotes%2520About%2520the%2520Chart%253A%2C50%2520mg%252Fkg%2520bw%252Fd%5C%22%3EIn%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20acceptable%20daily%20intake%20has%20been%20set%20at%2075%20sachets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20evidence%20have%20they%20used%20to%20come%20to%20this%20conclusion%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews%2Fitem%2F14-07-2023-aspartame-hazard-and-risk-assessment-results-released%5C%22%3EIARC%20looked%20closely%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.who.int%2Fmedia%2Fdocs%2Fdefault-source%2Fnutrition-and-food-safety%2Fjuly-13-final-summary-of-findings-aspartame.pdf%3Fsfvrsn%3Da531e2c1_5%26download%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Eevidence%20base%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20around%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20using%20data%20from%20observational%20studies%2C%20experimental%20studies%20and%20animal%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20there%20was%20some%20limited%20evidence%20in%20human%20studies%20linking%20aspartame%20and%20cancer%20(specifically%20liver%20cancer)%20and%20limited%20evidence%20from%20animal%20studies%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20considered%20the%20biological%20mechanism%20studies%20which%20showed%20how%20cancer%20may%20develop%20from%20the%20consumption%20of%20aspartame.%20Usually%20these%20are%20lab-based%20studies%20which%20show%20exactly%20how%20exposure%20to%20the%20agent%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20cancer.%20In%20this%20case%20they%20found%20there%20was%20limited%20evidence%20for%20how%20aspartame%20might%20cause%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20only%20three%20human%20studies%20that%20looked%20at%20cancer%20and%20aspartame%20intake.%20These%20large%20observational%20studies%20used%20the%20intake%20of%20soft%20drinks%20as%20an%20indicator%20of%20aspartame%20intake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20found%20a%20positive%20association%20between%20artificially%20sweetened%20beverages%20and%20liver%20cancer%20in%20either%20all%20of%20the%20population%20they%20were%20studying%20or%20sub-groups%20within%20them.%20But%20these%20studies%20could%20not%20rule%20out%20other%20factors%20that%20may%20have%20been%20responsible%20for%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6284800%2F%5C%22%3Econducted%20in%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%20followed%20475%2C000%20people%20for%2011%20years%20and%20found%20that%20each%20additional%20serve%20of%20diet%20soft%20drink%20consumed%20per%20week%20was%20linked%20to%20a%206%25%20increased%20risk%20of%20liver%20cancer.%20However%20the%20scientists%20did%20conclude%20that%20due%20to%20the%20rarity%20of%20liver%20cancer%20they%20still%20had%20small%20numbers%20of%20people%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F35728406%2F%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20study%20from%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20increased%20risk%20of%20liver%20cancer%20was%20seen%20in%20people%20with%20diabetes%20who%20drank%20more%20than%20two%20or%20more%20cans%20of%20a%20diet%20soda%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faacrjournals.org%2Fcebp%2Farticle%2F31%2F10%2F1907%2F709398%2FSugar-and-Artificially-Sweetened-Beverages-and%5C%22%3Ethird%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20from%20the%20US%2C%20found%20an%20increase%20in%20liver%20cancer%20risk%20in%20men%20who%20never%20smoked%20and%20drank%20two%20or%20more%20artificially%20sweetened%20drinks%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20this%20they%20have%20decided%20to%20declare%20aspartame%20as%20a%20Group%202b%20%E2%80%9Cpossible%20carcinogen%E2%80%9D.%20But%20they%20have%20also%20said%20more%20and%20better%20research%20is%20needed%20to%20further%20understand%20the%20relationship%20between%20aspartame%20and%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIARC%20has%20four%20categories%20(groupings)%20available%20for%20potential%20substances%20(or%20as%20they%20are%20referred%20to%20by%20IARC%2C%20%E2%80%9Cagents%E2%80%9D)%20that%20may%20cause%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cbr%3E%5CnWhat%20does%20each%20grouping%20mean%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGroup%201%20Carcinogenic%20to%20humans%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20an%20agent%20in%20this%20group%20is%20carcinogenic%2C%20which%20means%20there%20is%20convincing%20evidence%20from%20human%20studies%20and%20we%20know%20precisely%20%3Cem%3Ehow%3C%2Fem%3E%20it%20causes%20cancer.%20There%20are%20126%20agents%20in%20this%20group%2C%20including%20tobacco%20smoking%2C%20alcohol%2C%20processed%20meat%2C%20radiation%20and%20ionising%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGroup%202a%20Probably%20carcinogenic%20to%20humans%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20there%20are%20positive%20associations%20between%20the%20agent%20and%20cancer%20in%20humans%2C%20but%20there%20may%20still%20be%20other%20explanations%20for%20the%20association%20which%20were%20not%20fully%20examined%20in%20the%20studies.%20There%20are%2095%20agents%20in%20this%20group%2C%20including%20red%20meat%2C%20DDT%20insecticide%20and%20night%20shift%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGroup%202b%20Possibly%20carcinogenic%20in%20humans%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20this%20means%20limited%20evidence%20of%20causing%20cancer%20in%20humans%2C%20but%20sufficient%20evidence%20from%20animal%20studies%2C%20or%20the%20mechanism%20of%20how%20the%20agent%20may%20be%20carcinogenic%20is%20well%20understood.%20This%20basically%20means%20the%20current%20evidence%20indicates%20an%20agent%20may%20possibly%20be%20carcinogenic%2C%20but%20more%20scientific%20evidence%20from%20better%20conducted%20studies%20is%20needed.%20There%20are%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmonographs.iarc.who.int%2Fagents-classified-by-the-iarc%2F%5C%22%3E323%3C%2Fa%3E%20agents%20in%20this%20group%2C%20including%20aloe%20vera%20(whole%20leaf%20extract)%2C%20ginkgo%20biloba%20and%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGroup%203%20Not%20classifiable%20as%20a%20carcinogen%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20there's%20not%20enough%20evidence%20from%20humans%20or%20animals%2C%20and%20there%20is%20limited%20mechanistic%20evidence%20of%20how%20it%20may%20be%20a%20carcinogen.%20There%20are%20500%20agents%20in%20this%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ESo%20do%20I%20have%20to%20give%20up%20my%20diet%20soft%20drink%20habit%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20a%2070kg%20person%20you%20would%20need%20to%20consume%20about%2014%20cans%20(over%205%20litres)%20of%20soft%20drink%20sweetened%20with%20aspartame%20a%20day%20to%20reach%20the%20acceptable%20daily%20intake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20need%20to%20remember%20there%20may%20also%20be%20aspartame%20added%20in%20other%20foods%20consumed.%20So%20this%20is%20an%20unrealistic%20amount%20to%20consume%2C%20but%20not%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20need%20to%20consider%20all%20the%20evidence%20on%20aspartame%20together.%20The%20foods%20we%20typically%20see%20aspartame%20in%20are%20processed%20or%20ultra-processed%2C%20which%20have%20recently%20also%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fultra-processed-foods-are-trashing-our-health-and-the-planet-180115%5C%22%3Eshown%20to%20be%20detrimental%20to%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20artificial%20sweeteners%20(including%20aspartame)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC2892765%2F%23!po%3D59.3750%5C%22%3Ecan%20make%20people%20crave%20more%20sugar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20them%20want%20to%20eat%20more%20food%2C%20potentially%20causing%20them%20to%20gain%20more%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20together%2C%20this%20indicates%20we%20should%20be%20more%20careful%20about%20the%20amount%20of%20artificial%20sweeteners%20we%20consume%2C%20since%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-who-says-we-shouldnt-bother-with-artificial-sweeteners-for-weight-loss-or-health-is-sugar-better-205827%5C%22%3Edo%20not%20provide%20any%20health%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20have%20possible%20adverse%20effects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20overall%2C%20from%20this%20evidence%2C%20drinking%20the%20occasional%20or%20even%20daily%20can%20of%20a%20diet%20drink%20is%20safe%20and%20probably%20not%20a%20cancer%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECorrection%3A%20this%20article%20originally%20stated%20each%20serve%20of%20soft%20drink%20in%20a%20study%20was%20linked%20to%20a%206%25%20increased%20risk%20of%20liver%20cancer%2C%20however%20it%20was%20each%20additional%20serve%20per%20week.%20This%20has%20been%20amended.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F208844%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(Author%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fevangeline-mantzioris-153250%5C%22%3EEvangeline%20Mantzioris%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Program%20Director%20of%20Nutrition%20and%20Food%20Sciences%2C%2