s%20do%20not%20justify%20confident%20bets%20on%20the%20dollar's%20demise%2C%20because%20the%20greenback's%20centrality%20is%20mainly%20determined%20by%20economic%20factors%20and%20an%20incumbency%20advantage%20that%20is%20reinforced%20by%20network%20effects%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdollar-dominance-dedollarization-multipolar-order-atlantic-council-expert-china-yuan-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689364975000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b19658f9a259001947640c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fdollar-dominance-dedollarization-multipolar-order-atlantic-council-expert-china-yuan-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20dollar's%20dominance%20is%20determined%20by%20economic%20factors%20and%20not%20geopolitcal%20risk%2C%20Carla%20Norrl%C3%B6f%20of%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%20wrote%20in%20Project%20Syndicate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22fdemott%40insider.com%20(Filip%20De%20Mott)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fdollar-dominance-dedollarization-multipolar-order-atlantic-council-expert-china-yuan-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20an%20AI%20software%20engineer%20and%20I%20predict%20that%20most%20AI%20startups%20being%20funded%20today%20will%20die%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22artificial%20intelligence%20shutterstock%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5bfc6d54bde70f35572e2543%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20or%20A.I.%3Cp%3EShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20AI%20engineer%20says%20most%20people%20don't%20understand%20what%20AI%20can%20really%20do%20and%20what%20it%20can't%2C%20yet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThose%20working%20in%20AI%20understand%20when%20startup%20claims%20are%20realistic%20and%20when%20they're%20mostly%20hype.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20shares%20how%20he%20evaluates%20which%20startups%20he%20would%20use%2C%20invest%20in%20or%20work%20for%2C%20and%20which%20to%20avoid.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20an%20AI%20engineer%20who%20currently%20works%20for%20an%20AI%20legal%20startup%20and%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20identified%20because%20he%20is%20not%20authorized%20to%20speak%20about%20his%20work%20experiences.%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20employment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGenerative%20AI%20is%20just%20way%2C%20way%20overhyped%20right%20now%20and%20that%20means%20that%20many%20of%20the%20AI%20startups%20getting%20VC%20funding%20today%20are%20going%20to%20fail.%20This%20is%20going%20to%20be%20similar%20to%20what%20happened%20in%20crypto.%20There%20are%20going%20to%20be%20selective%20applications%20from%20startups%20that%20work%20well%20and%20can%20build%20businesses%2C%20but%20maybe%2070-80%25%20of%20them%20are%20going%20to%20die%20in%20the%20end.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20OpenAI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-usage-falling-students-summer-break-bad-sign-openai-microsoft-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20been%20experiencing%20declining%20usage%20lately%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20may%20indicate%20that%20generative%20AI%20chatbots%20won't%20take%20over%20the%20world.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20been%20working%20on%20AI%20systems%20for%20almost%20a%20decade%20and%20can%20tell%20you%20that%20we've%20seen%20all%20of%20this%20before.%20This%20is%20what%20happened%20to%20the%20self-driving%20car%20industry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20good%20as%20ChatGPT%20is%20at%20chatting%2C%20or%20Dall-E%20is%20at%20creating%20art%2C%20what%20these%20programs%20are%20doing%20is%20mimicking%20information%20they%20have%20ingested%20from%20the%20past.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday's%20AI%20can't%20really%20do%20what%20so%20many%20startups%20say%20their%20apps%20can%20do%20because%20AI%20can't%20reliably%20predict%20things.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Drive.ai%20self-driving%20car%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5d12ad602516e95aae6fec7b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223199%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrive.ai%20self-driving%20car%3Cp%3EDrive.ai%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20we%20got%20here%3A%20three%20waves%20of%20machine%20learning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere's%20been%2C%20so%20far%2C%20three%20waves%20of%20machine%20learning%20in%20AI%20development%20and%20each%20of%20them%20created%20a%20lot%20of%20startups.%20The%20three%20waves%20are%3A%20supervised%20learning%2C%20unsupervised%20learning%20and%20reinforced%20learning.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESupervised%20is%20when%20you%20are%20teaching%20the%20AI%20model%20how%20to%20do%20something%20like%20identify%20a%20pen.%20You%20hire%20a%20bunch%20of%20people%20to%20manually%20label%20photos%20of%20pens%20(and%20startups%20were%20born%20to%20do%20this)%20and%20you%20are%20training%20the%20model%20to%20answer%20the%20question%2C%20is%20this%20a%20pen%20or%20not%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnsupervised%20is%20when%20you%20are%20writing%20a%20rule%20in%20an%20algorithm%20and%20telling%20AI%20to%20detect%20what%20the%20object%20is.%20An%20example%20is%20pixel%20detection%20to%20identify%20colors%3A%20red%2C%20green%2C%20yellow%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReinforced%20learning%20is%20when%20you%20are%20training%20it%20to%20identify%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20an%20apple%2C%20and%20then%20reinforcing%20if%20it%20got%20it%20right%20or%20not.%20Is%20this%20an%20apple%3F%20Yes.%20Okay%2C%20great.%20Is%20this%20an%20apple%3F%20No%2C%20you%20got%20it%20wrong.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20AI%20engineering%20got%20into%20this%20steep%20learning%20curve%20based%20on%20all%20of%20it.%20It%20was%20reinforced%20and%20unsupervised%20combined%20together.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20I'm%20trying%20to%20get%20people%20outside%20the%20AI%20community%20to%20understand%20is%20that%20this%20is%20really%20essentially%20just%20a%20probability%20game.%20Like%20what%20is%20the%20highest%20probability%20that%20something%20will%20occur%20in%20the%20future%3F%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20self-driving%20car%20uses%20a%20bunch%20of%20deep%20learning%20models.%20When%20the%20model%20notices%20%26quot%3Boh%2C%20here's%20a%20human%20to%20the%20right%20of%20us.%20One%20second%20before%20I%20get%20to%20a%20nearby%20position%2C%20I%20need%20to%20predict%20if%20this%20person%20is%20going%20to%20move%20across%20the%20street%20or%20if%20this%20person%20is%20going%20to%20stay%20still.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20so%20it%20calculates%20all%20that%20based%20on%20postures%3A%20like%20if%20they're%20on%20their%20phone%20just%20standing%20still%2C%20most%20likely%20that%20person%20is%20not%20going%20to%20move.%20The%20probability%20of%20this%20person%20moving%20across%20the%20street%20is%20like%20maybe%2C%200.001%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20accidents%20end%20up%20occurring.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20that's%20what%20deep%20learning%20is%3A%20it's%20like%20a%20probabilistic%20prediction%20centric%20thing.%20And%20this%20is%20the%20day%20that%20we%20live%20in%20today.%20People%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20we're%20creating%20something%20new.%26quot%3B%20But%20all%20that%20is%2C%20even%20for%20something%20like%20OpenAI%2C%20is%20that%20they%20are%20feeding%20it%20so%20much%20data%20and%20then%20they're%20basically%20saying%2C%20replicate%20it%20and%20create%20something%20based%20on%20the%20previous%20information.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227144%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Future%20medical%20technology%20controlled%20by%20AI%20robot%20using%20machine%20learning%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F645e48ea11971c00188f1e41%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223174%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENanoStockk%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20you%20can%20and%20can't%20rely%20on%20AI%20to%20do%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYes%2C%20if%20you%20use%20that%20kind%20of%20AI%20correctly%2C%20it's%20super%20powerful.%20But%20AI%20wholly%20depends%20on%20the%20information%20fed%20to%20it.%20The%20information%20could%20be%20biased%2C%20or%20spitting%20out%20something%20that%20isn't%20creative%20but%20basically%20plagiarized%2C%20or%20based%20on%20old%20and%20outdated%20information.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20how%20can%20you%20tell%20if%20an%20AI%20startup's%20technology%20will%20work%20or%20if%20it%20and%20the%20company%20will%20likely%20fail%3F%20If%20what%20it's%20doing%20is%20reusing%20static%20information%20and%20doesn't%20rely%20on%20having%20to%20predict%20an%20outcome%2C%20it's%20on%20safer%20ground.%20Like%20routing%20a%20map%20in%20a%20controlled%20environment%20for%20warehouse%20robots.%20Unlike%20self-driving%20cars%2C%20warehouse%20robots%20work%20in%20a%20controlled%20environment%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOr%20call%20center%20triage%3A%20so%20anything%20that%20comes%20into%20the%20call%20center%20for%20an%20identified%20reason%2C%20machine%20learning%20can%20analyze%20that%20and%20route%20it%20to%20the%20correct%20person.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20startups%20that%20require%20heavy%20prediction%20will%20struggle%20to%20achieve%20their%20claims%2C%20just%20like%20most%20of%20the%20self-driving%20car%20startups%20from%20the%20last%20decade%20have%20not%20become%20big%20businesses%20(and%20we%20aren't%20all%20being%20driven%20around%20in%20them).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20bucket%20are%20startups%20with%20tech%20that%20relies%20on%20people%20changing%20their%20behavior%20to%20trust%20a%20machine%20instead%20of%20another%20human%20being%20like%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20virtual%20human%20apps%3A%20AI%20assistants%20that%20are%20supposed%20to%20replace%20a%20human%20to%20manage%20an%20executive's%20office%2C%20or%20AI%20bots%20that%20are%20supposed%20to%20replace%20salespeople.%20Another%20category%20is%20anything%20that%20requires%20strategy%2C%20like%20in%20the%20legal%20world%2C%20developing%20a%20defense.%20And%20another%20category%20is%20anything%20that%20requires%20the%20AI%20to%20understand%20and%20predict%20what%20people%20are%20feeling%2C%20like%20a%20concierge%20service.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20how%20can%20we%20bridge%20the%20gap%20between%20today's%20limited%20AI%20and%20a%20day%20when%20we%20can%20totally%20rely%20on%20it%3F%20Well%2C%20there%20is%20an%20intermediate%20solution.%20We%20can%20use%20AI%20today%20to%20do%20consistent%2C%20repetitive%20work%20%E2%80%93%20let's%20call%20that%20%26quot%3Bprework%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%93%20%3Cspan%3Eand%20include%20human%20beings%20in%20the%20process.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20there's%20a%20catch%20even%20for%20this%20because%20you%20also%20need%20to%20account%20for%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20AI%20adoption.%20Take%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Amazon%20Go.%20As%20of%20June%2C%20Amazon%20closed%20its%20ninth%20Go%20store%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-go-stores-closing-nyc-san-francisco-seattle-2023-3%5C%22%2