%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1233E%2Fproduction%2F_130385547_p0g0yc6v.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-66203569%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stars%20including%20Matt%20Damon%20and%20Florence%20Pugh%20left%20the%20premiere%20early%20as%20the%20strike%20was%20declared.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fentertainment-arts-66203569%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20Will%20'Severely%20Restrict%20Scope%20of%20RTI%20Act'%3A%20Activists%20Write%20to%20MPs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F02191508%2FParchment-bg.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20(DPDP)%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20amend%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act%20by%20%E2%80%9Cseverely%20restricting%20its%20scope%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20seeks%20to%20give%20%E2%80%9Cwide%20discretionary%20powers%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20both%20in%20rulemaking%20and%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20the%20oversight%20body%2C%20said%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%20(NCPRI)%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20members%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NCPRI%20has%20written%20to%20MPs%20highlighting%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20DPDP%20Bill%2C%20which%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20introduced%20in%20the%20upcoming%20monsoon%20session%20of%20parliament.%20The%20upcoming%20session%20is%20set%20to%20commence%20on%20July%2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20and%20note%20sent%20to%20MPs%20highlight%20several%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20DPDP%20Bill%20based%20on%20the%20draft%20which%20was%20made%20public%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20%26amp%3B%20Information%20Technology%20in%20November%202022%20(the%20draft%20approved%20by%20cabinet%20is%20not%20available%20in%20the%20public%20domain)%2C%20including%20the%20proposed%20changes%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20draft%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20(DPDP%20Bill)%20proposed%20by%20MeitY%20was%20expected%20to%20develop%20a%20framework%20balancing%20the%20need%20to%20protect%20certain%20kinds%20of%20personal%20data%20with%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%2C%20which%20lays%20out%20the%20statutory%20framework%20for%20Indian%20citizens%20to%20access%20information%2C%20including%20personal%20information.%20However%2C%20the%20draft%20Bill%20fails%20to%20safeguard%20and%20harmonise%20the%20two%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20amendment%20to%20Section%208(1)(j)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20seeks%20to%20exempt%20all%20personal%20information.%20It%20does%20away%20with%20the%20exceptions%20carved%20out%20within%20the%20Section%20based%20on%20which%20even%20personal%20information%20could%20have%20been%20disclosed.%20Currently%2C%20in%20order%20to%20deny%20personal%20information%2C%20at%20least%20one%20of%20the%20following%20grounds%20has%20to%20be%20proven%20%E2%80%93%20information%20sought%20has%20no%20relationship%20to%20any%20public%20activity%2C%20or%20information%20sought%20has%20no%20relationship%20to%20any%20public%20interest%2C%20or%20information%20sought%20would%20cause%20an%20unwarranted%20invasion%20of%20privacy%20and%20PIO%2Fappellate%20authority%20is%20satisfied%20that%20there%20is%20no%20larger%20public%20interest%20that%20justifies%20disclosure%2C%20the%20letter%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20proposed%20blanket%20exemption%20is%20especially%20problematic%20since%20it%20does%20not%20limit%20the%20exemption%20from%20disclosure%20to%20only%20sensitive%20personal%20information%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20continues%20to%20argue%20that%20the%20proposal%20to%20amend%20the%20RTI%20Act%20through%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20drafted%20based%20on%20an%20incorrect%20understanding%20of%20the%20RTI%20law.%20The%20draft%20Bill%20errs%20in%20interpreting%20the%20proviso%20to%20Section%208(1)%2C%20which%20states%20that%20%E2%80%9Cinformation%20which%20cannot%20be%20denied%20to%20the%20Parliament%20or%20a%20State%20Legislature%20shall%20not%20be%20denied%20to%20any%20person%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20being%20only%20applicable%20to%20Section%208(1)(j)%20and%20not%20to%20the%20whole%20of%20Section%208(1).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20perusal%20of%20the%20original%20gazette%20notification%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20shows%20that%20by%20virtue%20of%20its%20placement%20and%20indentation%2C%20it%20is%20applicable%20to%20all%20of%20Section%208(1)%20and%20not%20merely%20Section%208(1)(j).%20There%20are%20several%20judicial%20pronouncements%20to%20this%20effect%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20letter%20notes%20that%20it%20is%20well%20established%20that%20access%20to%20granular%20information%2C%20including%20personal%20information%2C%20is%20critical%20to%20empower%20people%20to%20undertake%20collective%20monitoring%20and%20ensure%20they%20are%20able%20to%20access%20their%20rights%20and%20entitlements.%20This%20principle%20is%20well%20recognised%20and%20has%20been%20adopted%20in%20various%20welfare%20programmes%20and%20schemes.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20proposed%20Bill%20will%20potentially%20place%20impediments%20and%20restrictions%20on%20such%20public%20disclosures.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20has%20been%20endorsed%20by%20prominent%20activists%20Anjali%20Bhardwaj%2C%20Venkatesh%20Nayak%2C%20Nikhil%20Dey%2C%20Rakesh%20Reddy%20Dubbudu%2C%20Pradip%20Pradhan%2C%20Pankti%20Jog%2C%20Dr.%20Shaikh%2C%20Aruna%20Roy%2C%20Shailesh%20Gandhi%2C%20Amrita%20Johri%2C%20Rolly%20Shivhare%2C%20Pradeep%20Raparia%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689345311000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F01%2F02191508%2FParchment-bg.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpersonal-data-protection-bill-will-severely-restrict-scope-of-rti-act-activists-write-to-mps%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples'%20Right%20to%20Information%20has%20written%20to%20MPs%20highlighting%20concerns%20regarding%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%20which%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20introduced%20in%20the%20upcoming%20monsoon%20session%20of%20parliament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fpersonal-data-protection-bill-will-severely-restrict-scope-of-rti-act-activists-write-to-mps%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hollywood%20actors-writers%20now%20on%20strike%20together%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689345000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101759853%2Cimgsize-79502.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fweb-stories%2Fdrew-barrymore-matt-damon-hollywood-actors-and-writers-now-on-strike-together%2Fphotostory%2F101759853.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F101759853.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3Edrew%20barrymore%2C%20matt%20damon%3A%20hollywood%20actors%20and%20writers%20now%20on%20strike%20together%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Arjun%20Pereira%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fweb-stories%2Fdrew-barrymore-matt-damon-hollywood-actors-and-writers-now-on-strike-together%2Fphotostory%2F101759853.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tiger's%20